Prospera OS
Audience Signals Specification v1.2

File: system/audience/audience-signals-v1.2.md
Status: Stable
Owner: Prospera Architecture Group
Category: System Specification

────────────────────────────────────────

1. Purpose

Audience Signals v1.2 define all allowable signals used for audience detection, classification, predictive scoring, and state transitions across Prospera OS.

This specification ensures:

• deterministic signal interpretation
• governance-approved signal sources
• zero unauthorized behavioral inference
• predictive drift detection
• multi-signal fusion aligned with PO2
• subsystem-safe routing of audience metadata

Audience Signals feed directly into:

• Audience Classifier v1.2
• Audience Matrix v1.2
• Audience State Machine v2.0
• Predictive Overlay v2.0
• Safety Envelope v2.0
• Routing System v1.2

────────────────────────────────────────

2. Scope

Included:

• definition of allowable signals
• signal categories
• signal normalization rules
• permitted signal sources
• prohibited signals
• governance validation
• predictive integration

Excluded:

• psychological inference
• emotion decoding
• user profiling
• marketing or personalization signals

────────────────────────────────────────

3. Signal Architecture (v1.2)

Audience Signals consist of four deterministic categories:

3.1 Identity Signals

• identity completeness
• verification status
• identity history consistency
• SSOT lineage continuity

3.2 Contextual Signals

• request metadata
• subsystem origin
• frequency + stability
• environment markers (non-personal)

3.3 Behavioral Stability Signals

• sequence stability (non-behavioral inference)
• interaction variance
• temporal coherence

3.4 Predictive Risk Signals (PO2)

• drift indicators
• anomaly markers
• multi-signal fusion risk score
• constitutional boundary markers

────────────────────────────────────────

4. Allowed vs Prohibited Signals
4.1 Allowed Signals

Allowed signals are deterministic, non-personal, non-psychological, and governance-approved.

Examples:

• subsystem intent metadata
• workload patterns
• interaction context
• identity trust level (non-sensitive)
• Envelope v2.0 flags
• predictive risk metrics (0-1.0)

4.2 Prohibited Signals

Strictly forbidden:

• emotional inference
• psychological profiling
• demographic inference
• personality prediction
• health, medical, or personal traits
• social attribute inference
• inferred sentiment or tone

Any prohibited signal → must trigger:

• Envelope BLOCK
• Class → D
• ASM2 → ESCALATED

────────────────────────────────────────

5. Signal Data Model
AudienceSignal
AudienceSignal {
  type: Identity | Context | Stability | Predictive,
  value: any,
  timestamp: ISO8601,
  source: subsystem,
  ssot_seed: string
}

NormalizedSignal
NormalizedSignal {
  signal_type: string,
  normalized_value: number | string,
  risk_weight: number,
  ssot_hash: string
}

SignalBundle
SignalBundle {
  identity: [NormalizedSignal],
  context: [NormalizedSignal],
  stability: [NormalizedSignal],
  predictive: [NormalizedSignal],
  fusion_score: number
}


────────────────────────────────────────

6. Signal Normalization Rules (v1.2)

All signals must be:

• deterministic
• reproducible
• bounded
• non-probabilistic unless part of PO2
• fully aligned with Kernel Constitutional Rules v1.2

Normalization steps:

validate allowable type

convert to canonical numeric/string value

apply risk weighting

compute ssot_hash

feed into fusion pipeline (PO2)

────────────────────────────────────────

7. Predictive Overlay v2.0 Integration

Signals feed into PO2 using:

• Weighted fusion
• Anomaly detection models
• Drift scoring
• Governance-aligned risk interpretation

Output:

fusion_score (0–1.0)
risk_level: LOW | MEDIUM | HIGH | CRITICAL


Fusion rules:

If prohibited signal detected → risk = CRITICAL
If drift_score > 0.8 → escalate to Governance


────────────────────────────────────────

8. Governance Rules

Governance Layer must audit:

• signal legality
• source subsystem validity
• lineage consistency
• Envelope v2.0 compliance
• constitutional markers

Any deviation → require HOLD state in ASM2.

────────────────────────────────────────

9. Subsystem Integration

Audience Signals integrate with:

• Classifier — feature vector input
• Matrix — capability boundary enforcement
• ASM2 — transition triggers
• Routing — operational constraints
• Safety — governance gating

No module may use signals for personalization or behavioral inference.

────────────────────────────────────────

10. Versioning

v1.0 Initial signal definition
v1.1 Predictive integration
v1.2 PO2 alignment + constitutional restrictions + deterministic normalization

